- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper deals with one-way functions, which are a fundamental concept in cryptography. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the properties a combinatorial problem should have in order to hold a complete one-way function, which is related to algorithmic complexity. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper discusses the completeness of one-way functions. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also possible as the paper discusses the concept of completeness in the context of information theory. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the proof of completeness for the one-way functions.
